|| {{sortname|Donald|Trump}} || [[New York City]]|| New York ||{{sort|45|(45th) January 20, 2017 \u2013 [[Incumbent]]}}\n|- style=\"background:#ffffff;\"\n| {{dts|July 6, 1946}} || {{sortname|George W.|Bush}}  || [[New Haven, Connecticut|New Haven]] || [[Connecticut]] || {{sort|43|(43rd) January 20, 2001 \u2013 January 20, 2009}}\n|- style=\"background:#ffffff;\"\n| {{dts|August 19, 1946}} || {{sortname|Bill|Clinton}} || [[Hope, Arkansas|Hope]] || [[Arkansas]] || {{sort|42|(42nd) January 20, 1993 \u2013 January 20, 2001}}\n|- style=\"background:#ffffff;\"\n| {{dts|August 4, 1961}} ||{{sortname|Barack H.|Obama}} ||[[Honolulu]]||[[Hawaii]]||{{sort|44|(44th) January 20, 2009 \u2013 January 20, 2017}}\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| colspan=\"5\" | <center><small>'''{{note label|julian_date|*||Gregorian date; Julian date is April 2, 1743}}<ref>https://charlottesville.guide/jeffersons-tombstone/</ref>'''</small></center>\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| colspan=\"5\" | <center><small>'''{{note label|state_colony|\u2020||Colony, pre\u20131776, rather than state.}}'''</small></center>\n|}\n\n== Presidential birthplace and early childhood historic sites ==\nThe birthplaces and early childhood residences of many U.S. presidents have been preserved or replicated. In instances where a physical structure is absent, a monument or roadside marker has been erected to denote the site's historic significance. All sites in the table below are listed in the [[National Register of Historic Places]].\n\nA dramatic shift in childbirth from home to hospital occurred in the United States in the early 20th century (mid\u20131920s to 1940).<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Thomasson|first1=Melissa A.|last2=Treber|first2=Jaret|date=January 2008|title=From home to hospital: The evolution of childbirth in the United States, 1928-1940|journal=Explorations in Economic History|location=Amsterdam, Netherlands|publisher=Elsevier|volume=45|issue=1|pages=76\u201399|doi=10.1016/j.eeh.2007.07.001}}</ref> Reflective of this trend, all presidents born after [[World War II]] (Bill Clinton and every president since) have been born in a hospital, not a private residence. This sortable table is ordered by the presidents' birthdates.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!President\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Image\n!Historic site\n|-\n|[[George Washington]]\n|{{sort|01|[[File:Geo Washington birthplace.jpg|100px]]}}\n|[[George Washington Birthplace National Monument]], [[Colonial Beach, Virginia]]\n|-\n|[[John Adams]]\n|{{sort|02|[[File:John Adams birthplace, Quincy, Massachusetts.JPG|100px]]}}\n|[[John Adams Birthplace]], [[Quincy, Massachusetts]]\n|-\n|[[James Madison]]\n|{{sort|03|[[File:Belle Grove house.jpg|105px]]}}\n|[[Belle Grove (Port Conway, Virginia)|Belle Grove Plantation]], Port Conway, Virginia\n|-\n|[[James Monroe]]\n|{{sort|04|[[File:James Monroe Family Home Site - Stierch.JPG|100px]]}}\n|[[James Monroe Family Home Site]], Colonial Beach, Virginia\n|-\n|[[John Quincy Adams]]\n|{{sort|05|[[File:John Quincy Adams birthplace, Quincy, Massachusetts.JPG|100px]]}}\n|[[John Quincy Adams Birthplace]], Quincy, Massachusetts\n|-\n|[[William Henry Harrison]]\n|{{sort|06|[[File:Berkeley plantation harrison home.jpg|100px]]}}\n|[[Berkeley Plantation]], Charles City County, Virginia\n|-\n|[[John Tyler]]\n|{{sort|07|[[File:Greenway, State Route 5 vicinity, Charles City vicinity (Charles City County, Virginia).jpg|100px]]}}\n|[[Greenway Plantation]], Charles City County, Virginia\n|-\n|[[James Buchanan]]\n|{{sort|07.5|[[File:Buchanan's Birthplace State Park.jpg|100px]]}}\n|[[Buchanan's Birthplace State Park]], Cove Gap, Pennsylvania\n|-\n|[[James K. Polk]]\n|<center>{{sort|08|[[File:James K. Polk Childhood Log Cabin (Reconstruction).jpg|100px]]}}</center>\n|[[President James K. Polk Historic Site]], Pineville, North Carolina\n|-\n|[[Franklin Pierce]]\n|{{sort|08|[[File:HillsboroughNH FranklinPierceHomestead.jpg|100px]]}}\n|[[Franklin Pierce Homestead]], Hillsborough, New Hampshire\n|-\n|[[Abrah