J&pg=PA759&dq=Popular+Science+1930+plane+%22Popular+Mechanics%22&hl=en&ei=fxBvTp7pAoyhtwfhqq33CQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CEQQ6AEwBzgU#v=onepage&q&f=true \"Arch Bridge in Australia to Have Record Span\", ''Popular Mechanics'', May 1929]\n* [http://nla.gov.au/nla.pic-vn3307575 Air views of the opening celebrations, 19 March 1932] / photographed by W. E. Searle\n* [http://nla.gov.au/nla.pic-an23148082 Sydney Harbour Bridge during the Olympic Games, 19\u201326 September 2000] / Loui Seselja\n* [http://sigmatestudio.com/2009/10/sydney-harbour-bridge-grass-picnic/ Picnic on Sydney Harbour Bridge] / Sigmate Studio\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20091029161036/http://www.boudist.com/archive/2009/10/25/breakfast-sydney-harbour-bridge.php Breakfast on the Bridge] / Daniel Boud\n* [http://nla.gov.au/nla.pic-an14156869 Buildings and roads around North Sydney and Sydney Harbour Bridge, 1958\u20131961] / Wolfgang Sievers\n\n{{Bridges in Sydney |state=autocollapse}}\n{{Road infrastructure in Sydney}}\n{{Sydney landmarks}}\n{{Architecture of Sydney |state=autocollapse}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sydney Harbour Bridge}}\n[[Category:Australian National Heritage List]]\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 1932]]\n[[Category:Bridges in Sydney]]\n[[Category:Historic Civil Engineering Landmarks]]\n[[Category:Railway bridges in New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Road-rail bridges]]\n[[Category:Sydney Harbour]]\n[[Category:Sydney New Year's Eve]]\n[[Category:Through arch bridges in Australia]]\n[[Category:Toll bridges in Australia]]\n[[Category:Toll roads in Australia]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Sydney]]\n[[Category:1932 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Roads with a reversible lane]]\n[[Category:Milsons Point]]\n[[Category:New South Wales State Heritage Register]]\n[[Category:Dawes Point, New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Articles incorporating text from the New South Wales State Heritage Register]]\n[[Category:Sydney central business district]]\n[